## Description {#details}

Base class for non-instruction debug metadata records that have positions within IR.

Features various methods copied across from the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instruction">Instruction</a> class to aid ease-of-use. DbgRecords should always be linked into a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dbgmarker">DbgMarker</a>&#39;s StoredDbgRecords list. The marker connects a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dbgrecord">DbgRecord</a> back to its position in the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a>.

We need a discriminator for dyn/isa casts. In order to avoid paying for a vtable for &quot;virtual&quot; functions too, subclasses must add a new discriminator value (RecordKind) and cases to a few functions in the base class: deleteRecord clone isIdenticalToWhenDefined both print methods createDebugIntrinsic

Definition at line 134 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/debugprograminstruction-h">DebugProgramInstruction.h</a>.
